{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"c254fb1e-6788-5fd3-9748-44f6b23972ab","excerpt":"Intro I was reflecting on last Summer and spending quality time with the boys‚Ä¶ coding . ‚ù§Ô∏èand they had a blast learning and building It was‚Ä¶","html":"<h2 id=\"intro\"><a href=\"#intro\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Intro</h2>\n<p>I was reflecting on last Summer and spending quality time with the boys‚Ä¶<strong><em>coding</em></strong>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>‚ù§Ô∏èand they had a blast learning and building</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It was cool to find that my boys share a passion for creating, <em>just like their dad</em>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"hardware\"><a href=\"#hardware\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hardware</h2>\n<p>I needed cheap hardware since at this point I didn‚Äôt know if this would just be a phase.</p>\n<p>üí∞I didn‚Äôt want to spend more than $100 on a PC and monitor.</p>\n<p>I had already put together a Raspberry Pi for my home networking which is a blog post on its own. So I thought that this would be an excellent solution for my boys as well.</p>\n<p>I found a BOGO offer on Pis from Arrow Electronics. While you can just <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B01C6EQNNK/ref=oh_aui_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&#x26;psc=1\">buy the entire kit from Amazon</a>, these did not include the fans, case, or power adapter. So if your just looking for a kit, <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07BTHNW9W/ref=oh_aui_search_asin_title?ie=UTF8&#x26;psc=1\">Amazon has those too</a>.</p>\n<p>So at the end of the day, you will need:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Raspberry Pi</li>\n<li>Case</li>\n<li>Fan and Heatsinks(optional)</li>\n<li>Power Adapter</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"setup\"><a href=\"#setup\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Setup</h2>\n<h2 id=\"coding\"><a href=\"#coding\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Coding</h2>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>","frontmatter":{"title":"Learning Scratch on the Raspberry Pi","date":"February 04, 2019","slug":"learning-scratch-on-the-rpi","language":"en","tags":["linux","programming","family time"],"cover":null,"imageTw":null,"imageFb":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"learning-scratch-on-the-rpi","previous":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Habits to be a Better Developer","slug":"habits-to-be-a-better-developer","type":null,"tags":["habits","self-development"]}},"next":null}}